cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.CC, cs.LO 

Reasoning: 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with regular operations on languages and their state complexity. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper uses derivatives to calculate upper bounds on quotient complexity. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper discusses the complexity of languages. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper finds tight upper bounds on the quotient complexity of regular operations on ideal languages. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is also relevant as the paper deals with regular languages and their properties.
